# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/semiotical
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/semiotical> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/semiotical> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The base of all semiotic relations."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/semiotical> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "semiotical"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/semiotical> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "Semiotic relations can be seen as shortcuts that replaces a series of complex causal relations with a single relation."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/semiotical> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "Semiotic relations take part in a triadic semiotic meaning-making process, where an 'interpreter' connects a 'sign' (e.g. a property) to an entity (called 'referent')."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/semiotical> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "The semiotic relations in the SSbD Core Ontology are inspirred by EMMO, which in turn is based on the semiotic theory by Charles Sanders Peirce (1839-1914)."@en .
