_:genid7 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/hasPart> .
_:genid7 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Dataset> <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/usageNote> "A collection of (more than one) datum, published or curated by a single agent, and available for access or download in one or more representations."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Dataset> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Encoded data made of more than one datum."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Dataset> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Dataset"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/DateData
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DateData> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DateData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/SymbolicData> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DateData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema11-2/#date> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DateData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A symbolic data representing date. Format: YYYY-MM-DD (followed by an optional time zone offset, e.g. +01:00 for Central Europe)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DateData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "DateData"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/DateTimeData
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DateTimeData> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DateTimeData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/SymbolicData> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DateTimeData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema11-2/#dateTime> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DateTimeData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A symbolic data representing datetime. Format: YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss (followed by an optional time zone offset, e.g. +01:00 for Central Europe)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DateTimeData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "DateTimeData"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Datum
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Datum> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Datum> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Data> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Datum> <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/usageNote> "Datum is the building block of datasets."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Datum> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A self-consistent encoded data entity."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Datum> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Datum"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Description
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Description> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Description> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Sign> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Description> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A collection of properties that depicts an object."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Description> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Description"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Description> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "A description is not atomic in the sense that it is made of more than one property."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/DomainOfApplicabilityStatus
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DomainOfApplicabilityStatus> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DomainOfApplicabilityStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Property> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DomainOfApplicabilityStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A result of a model or software indicating whether an input is within the applicability domain of the model or software. Applicability domain refers to the range of conditions and limitations within which a model can be reliably applied. It is a critical factor in determining the accuracy and validity of a model, as it defines the scope of its predictions and identifies potential sources of uncertainty. The process of defining the applicability domain involves assessing the model's performance under different conditions and establishing the boundaries of its predictive capabilities."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DomainOfApplicabilityStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "DomainOfApplicabilityStatus"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DomainOfApplicabilityStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "It should take one of the following values: ssbd:undefined; ssbd:outOfDomain; ssbd:inDomain."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/DoubleData
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DoubleData> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DoubleData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/NumericalData> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DoubleData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema11-2/#double> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DoubleData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A symbolic data representing a 64-bit floating point numbers incl. ±Inf, ±0, NaN."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/DoubleData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "DoubleData"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/FloatData
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/FloatData> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/FloatData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/NumericalData> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/FloatData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema11-2/#float> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/FloatData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A symbolic data representing a 32-bit floating point numbers incl. ±Inf, ±0, NaN."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/FloatData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "FloatData"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Indicator
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Indicator> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Indicator> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Property> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Indicator> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Descriptor"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Indicator> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "EndPoint"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Indicator> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A property that provides information about the state of a system. It simplifies complex realities into measurable values that can guide decisions."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Indicator> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "For a computation is an indicator a specific property/datum that is provided in the output."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Indicator> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Indicator"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Indicator> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "A precisely defined variable intended to reflect an outcome of interest that is statistically analyzed to address a particular research question. A precise definition of an endpoint typically specifies the type of assessments made, the timing of those assessments, the assessment tools used, and possibly other details, as applicable, such as how multiple assessments within an individual are to be combined.\n\n-- National Library of Medicine, https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK338448/\n"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Information
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Information> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Information> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Data> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Information> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Sign> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Information> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "Luciano Floridi, Information - A Very Short Introduction, Oxford University Press (2010) ISBN: 9780199551378"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Information> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Data with meaning (semiotic sign)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Information> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Information"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/IntData
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/IntData> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/IntData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/LongData> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/IntData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema11-2/#int> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/IntData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A data representing a 32-bit integer number."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/IntData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "IntData"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/IntegerData
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/IntegerData> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/IntegerData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/NumericalData> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/IntegerData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema11-2/#integer> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/IntegerData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A data representing an arbritrary sized integer number."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/IntegerData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "IntegerData"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Interpreter
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Interpreter> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Interpreter> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Agent> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Interpreter> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The agent that connects the sign to an entity in a semiotic (meaning-making) process."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Interpreter> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "A person (interpreter) that measures the length (sign) of an pencil (object)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Interpreter> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Interpreter"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/LongData
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/LongData> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/LongData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/IntegerData> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/LongData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema11-2/#long> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/LongData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A data representing a 64-bit integer number."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/LongData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "LongData"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/MaterialProcess
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/MaterialProcess> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/MaterialProcess> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Process> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/MaterialProcess> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A process that has material as input and output."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/MaterialProcess> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "MaterialProcess"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Matter
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Matter> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Matter> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Entity> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Matter> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An entity that possess mass and occupies volume."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Matter> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Matter"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Matter> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "From the definition it follows that matter is an object with fermionic parts."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Matter> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "The interpretation of the term \"matter\" is not univocal. Several concepts are labelled with this term, depending on the field of science. The concept mass is sometimes related to the term \"matter\", even if the former refers to a physical quantity (precisely defined by modern physics) while the latter is a type that qualifies a physical entity.\nIt is possible to identify more than one concept that can be reasonably labelled with the term \"matter\". For example, it is possible to label as matter only the entities that are made up of atoms. Or more generally, we can be more fine-grained and call \"matter\" the entities that are made up of protons, neutrons or electrons, so that we can call matter also a neutron radiation or a cathode ray.\nA more fundamental approach taken here, considers matter as entities that are made of quarks and leptons, without excluding particles like the W and Z bosons that possess some mass, but are not fermions. This definition also include antimatter."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Measurement
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Measurement> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Measurement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Process> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Measurement> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An observation that results in a quantitative comparison of a 'property' of an 'object' with a standard reference based on a well defined mesurement procedure."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Measurement> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Measurement"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Model
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Model> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Model> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Sign> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Model> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A useful simplified description of a selected part of the world."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Model> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Newton's law of motion is a model for how a body will move when subjected to forces.\nA mouse can be seen as a model for a human (e.g. in medicine).\nAn architectural floor plan is a model of a house.\n"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Model> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Model"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Model> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "A model is a sign that resembles or imitates an object, in shape, function or by sharing a similar logical structure."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/NumericalData
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/NumericalData> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/NumericalData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/SymbolicData> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/NumericalData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A symbolic data representing a numerical value."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/NumericalData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "NumericalData"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Object
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Object> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Object> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Entity> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Object> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Continuant"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Object> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Endurant"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Object> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An entity that has a temporal extension."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Object> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Object"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Object> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "Object individals will typically also be an individual of 'Matter'. However, when categorising something as an 'Object', the focus is on its existence (throughout one of more processes), while 'Matter' focuses on that it pocess mass and takes up volume and how it can further be categorised as "@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Object> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "Object is the class of all individuals who's temporal parts are of the same type as the whole."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Participant
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Participant> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Participant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Agent> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Participant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Object> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Participant> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An object that participates to a process."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Participant> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "A student during an examination. The student exists both before and after the examination."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Participant> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Participant"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Participant> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "Mereologically participation means that the object is a spatial part of the process."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Process
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Process> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Process> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Activity> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Process> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Occurent"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Process> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Perdurant"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Process> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An activity with temporal parts."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Process> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Process"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Process> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "The temporal parts of a process are not of the same type as the process itself."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Profiler
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Profiler> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Profiler> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Software> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Profiler> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A software that identify the affiliation of the target chemical(s) to preliminary defined categories (functional groups/alerts)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Profiler> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Profiler"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Profiler> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "The outcome of the profiling determines the most appropriate way to search for analogues, but they are also useful for preliminary screening or prioritization of substances."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Property
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Property> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Property> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Sign> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Property> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An \"atomic\" sign that stands for a characteristic of an object that can be observed or detected in a semiotic process."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Property> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Property"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Property> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "A property is atomic in the sense that is aimed to deliver one and one only aspect of the object."@en .
