# https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDAssessment
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Assessment> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> _:genid9 .
_:genid9 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#someValuesFrom> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDDimension> .
_:genid9 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/assesses> .
_:genid9 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> _:genid10 .
_:genid10 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#someValuesFrom> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/SpecifiedAssessment> .
_:genid10 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/hasPart> .
_:genid10 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#altLabel> "SSbD Assessment"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An assessment of the safety and sustainability of chemicals and materials across their life cycle. Assesses one or more ssbd dimension, through one ore more SSbDSpecifiedAssessments"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "SSbDAssessment"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDDimension
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDDimension> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDDimension> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Entity> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDDimension> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/source> "https://www.oecd.org/content/dam/oecd/en/publications/reports/2022/10/sustainability-and-safe-and-sustainable-by-design-working-descriptions-for-the-safer-innovation-approach_1ba68750/a9a80171-en.pdf" .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDDimension> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Safe and Sustainable by Design Dimension" .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDDimension> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Safe and sustainable by design (SSbD) can be described as an approach that focuses on providing a function (or service), while avoiding onerous environmental footprints and chemical properties that may be harmful to human health or the environment.  In essence, the SSbD approach aims to identifying and minimizing, at an early phase of the innovation process, the impacts concerning safety for humans and the environment and for sustainability, minimizing the environmental footprint, in particular regarding climate change and resource use and, protecting ecosystems and biodiversity, taking a lifecycle perspective. The SSbD approach addresses the safety and sustainability of the material/ chemical/ product and associated processes along the whole life cycle, including all the steps of the research and development (R&D) phase, production, use, recycling, and disposal."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDDimension> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "SSbDDimension"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SSbDDimension> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "The superclass of all dimensions relevant for SSbD assessments." .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/ShortData
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/ShortData> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/ShortData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/IntData> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/ShortData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema11-2/#short> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/ShortData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A data representing a 16-bit integer number."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/ShortData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "ShortData"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Sign
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Sign> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Sign> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Entity> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Sign> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A sign that stands for an entity."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Sign> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Sign"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Sign> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "A sign is a part of a triadic semiotic (meaning-making) process, where an 'interpreter' connects a 'sign' to an entity (called 'referent')."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Software
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Software> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Software> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Data> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Software> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "All or part of the programs, procedures, rules, and associated documentation of an information processing system."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Software> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Software"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/SpecifiedAssessment
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SpecifiedAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SpecifiedAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Assessment> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SpecifiedAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An assessment that is focused on a specific aspect or dimension of safety and sustainability, such as functionality, safety, or environmental impact."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SpecifiedAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "SpecifiedAssessment"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/SymbolicData
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SymbolicData> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SymbolicData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Data> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SymbolicData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://www.w3.org/TR/2012/REC-owl2-syntax-20121211/#Datatype_Maps> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SymbolicData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://www.w3.org/TR/2012/REC-xmlschema11-2-20120405/#built-in-datatypes> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SymbolicData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The class for entities which stands for a specific data format expressed using a symbolic encoding."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/SymbolicData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "SymbolicData"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/TierLevel
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/TierLevel> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/TierLevel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Entity> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/TierLevel> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Represent a tiered, iterative framework for evaluating chemical and material safety from early innovation to production."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/TierLevel> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "TierLevel"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/TierLevel> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "This approach typically involves a three-tier system-ranging from qualitative, early-stage, in silico, and in vitro screening to, finally, advanced, quantitative, in vivo testing."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/TimeData
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/TimeData> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/TimeData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/SymbolicData> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/TimeData> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema11-2/#time> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/TimeData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A symbolic data representing time. Format: hh:mm:ss (followed by an optional time zone offset, e.g. +01:00 for Central Europe)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/TimeData> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "TimeData"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ssbd/Toxicity
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Toxicity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Toxicity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/ssbd/Indicator> .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Toxicity> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A descriptor for a substance to cause harmful health effects."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Toxicity> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Toxicity"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Toxicity> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "The helth effects can strike a single cell, a group of cells, an organ system, or the entire body. A toxic effect may be visible damage, or a decrease in performance or function measurable only by a test."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ssbd/Toxicity> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "Toxicity is always related to a given measurement procedure. Hence, the user is expected to define spesific subclasses defining the measurement procedure that the toxicity is measured according to."@en .
